Bodies Of 11 Infants Found In Shuttered Funeral Home's Ceiling|http://www.huffingtonpost.com.au|http://www.huffingtonpost.com.au/2018/10/13/bodies-of-11-infants-found-in-shuttered-funeral-homes-ceiling_a_23560084/?utm_hp_ref=au-homepage||2018-10-13|Hilary Hanson,Editor,The Huffington Post||UPDATE: Oct. 16 ― Police clarified at a press conference on Monday that the remains appeared to be 10 fetuses and one full-term baby, the Detroit Free Press reported. Officers also said they would be opening a criminal investigation into the situation.

PREVIOUSLY:

Law enforcement has recovered the remains of an 11 infants hidden in a false ceiling inside a Detroit funeral home that was shuttered earlier this year.

The bodies were located inside a “hidden false ceiling between the first and second floor of the funeral home,” Detroit Police Lt. Detective Brian Bowser said during a Friday press conference, part of which was posted on Twitter by Detroit News reporter Sarah Rahal. Bowser added that police do not know why the bodies were stowed in the ceiling.
